data.message: Some good news reading: teams at the Chan Zuckerberg Initiative and Biohub have been building IDseq -- an open source infectious disease genetic sequencing tool that can serve as an early warning system around the world. We were building it when Covid hit, and in Cambodia it was used to confirm the country's first case and inform their prevention efforts.
I'm grateful to get to build things that so many people find meaningful in their lives.
Thanks @adam.the.creator for designing my next board. The sun never stood a chance.
New commerce features coming to support businesses and make shopping easier: Shops on WhatsApp and Marketplace, Instagram Visual Search and Shops Ads. More detail in the comments.
